{"word":"H804 - אַשּׁוּר - ʼAshshûwr - ash-shoor' - Asshur","slug":"H804","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אַשּׁוּר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼAshshûwr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ash-shoor'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Asshur"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05E9;&#x05BC;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D0;&#x05E9;&#x05BC;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E8; - 'ashshu&#x0302;r  'ashshu&#x0302;r</b> - <i>ash-shoor', ash-shoor'</i><p/>Apparently from <a href=\"#/H833\">H833</a> (in the sense of <i>successful</i>); <i>Ashshur</i>, the second son of Shem; also his descendants and the country occupied by them (that is, Assyria), its region and its empire: - Asshur, Assur, Assyria, Assyrians. See <a href=\"#/H838\">H838</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2977\">H2977</a>, <a href=\"#/H803\">H803</a>, <a href=\"#/H805\">H805</a>, <a href=\"#/H807\">H807</a>, <a href=\"#/H810\">H810</a>, <a href=\"#/H811\">H811</a>, <a href=\"#/H812\">H812</a>, <a href=\"#/H813\">H813</a>"}]}